Following the recent suicide bomb attack in Gwoza, Borno State recently, the Yobe State Police Command has urged people in the state to report suspicious persons and movement or objects to the nearest police station. The Command gave the warning in a statement issued on Wednesday by its Public Relations Officer, Dungus Abdulkarim. It said, “Yobe State Police Command has received with concern the news of the recent suicide bomb attack in a Mosque in Gwoza LGA of Borno State where four (4) persons died as a result of the attack. “In lieu of the news, Yobe State Police Command as a matter of precaution is calling on the general public to be vigilant and beware of suspicious behaviour of persons that may be dangerous as the war against insurgency is still ongoing.”